This command seems to work well as a `package.json` post install step. 

```json
{
  "main": "index.js",
  "scripts": {
    "postinstall": "npm rebuild grpc --target=6.1.0 --target_arch=x64 --target_platform=linux --target_libc=glibc"
  },
}
```

Just to be clear, you must create a new file called `package.json` and then add the following code to the file 
`{
  "main": "index.js",
  "scripts": {
    "postinstall": "npm rebuild grpc --target=6.1.0 --target_arch=x64 --target_platform=linux --target_libc=glibc"
  },
}
`

Then compressing it with the rest of the files? Because the problem still persists for me after doing that! Trying to link Firebase and Lambda, but I can't get passed this error!
